1
00:00:05,631 --> 00:00:07,231
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,301 --> 00:00:09,041
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:09,571 --> 00:00:10,641
(Hanguk University Hospital)

4
00:00:10,701 --> 00:00:12,371
(Episode 49)

5
00:00:20,781 --> 00:00:23,951
(Ward A)

6
00:00:26,921 --> 00:00:30,821
Hyun Bin is busy today,
so I came instead.

7
00:00:32,461 --> 00:00:34,531
I only brought things
the hospital said were okay,

8
00:00:34,591 --> 00:00:37,101
so you don't have to worry. And...

9
00:00:37,901 --> 00:00:38,931
Here.

10
00:00:39,231 --> 00:00:41,231
As a matter of fact,
my hair's been thinning,

11
00:00:41,531 --> 00:00:42,771
so I needed this.

12
00:00:44,171 --> 00:00:45,371
Want me to put it on for you?

13
00:00:46,041 --> 00:00:48,271
(Ward B)

14
00:00:48,841 --> 00:00:51,141
That color looks great on you.

15
00:00:51,781 --> 00:00:54,051
I'm going to take a picture
and show it to Hyun Bin.

16
00:00:55,751 --> 00:00:57,551
Ta-da.

17
00:01:02,661 --> 00:01:03,661
My goodness...

18
00:01:04,391 --> 00:01:05,391
Se Ri?

19
00:01:06,031 --> 00:01:07,161
Oh, you're here.

20
00:01:18,811 --> 00:01:19,841
Father.

21
00:01:19,911 --> 00:01:21,541
(Hanguk University Hospital)

22
00:01:22,411 --> 00:01:23,881
I can't believe you.

23
00:01:25,781 --> 00:01:28,581
- How did you find out?
- What do you mean, "how?"

24
00:01:29,451 --> 00:01:32,251
The real estate agent called me,
so I got suspicious.

25
00:01:32,351 --> 00:01:35,621
I asked Hyun Bin what was going on
and called to chew him out.

26
00:01:36,461 --> 00:01:40,531
That real estate agent is useless.
I told him not to tell...

27
00:01:44,261 --> 00:01:46,171
I'll go get some more water.

28
00:02:07,621 --> 00:02:08,661
Are you upset?

29
00:02:09,861 --> 00:02:10,861
No.

30
00:02:14,061 --> 00:02:16,061
Because I know why
you didn't tell me.

31
00:02:17,501 --> 00:02:19,701
- It's nothing serious.
- Of course.

32
00:02:24,571 --> 00:02:26,341
It had better be nothing serious,
Father.

33
00:02:27,741 --> 00:02:29,041
You know that, right, Father?

34
00:02:30,311 --> 00:02:32,381
You're the pillar of our family.

35
00:02:33,181 --> 00:02:36,781
Father, I'll do anything you ask.

36
00:02:38,251 --> 00:02:39,251
So...

37
00:02:40,021 --> 00:02:42,921
You have to get well soon, Father.
Okay?

38
00:02:46,431 --> 00:02:47,491
What am I going to do?

39
00:02:49,131 --> 00:02:51,201
What am I going to do, Father?

40
00:02:56,841 --> 00:02:59,271
What am I going to do, Father?

41
00:03:02,911 --> 00:03:04,911
(Admissions And Payment)

42
00:03:14,091 --> 00:03:15,121
It's strange, isn't it?

43
00:03:18,061 --> 00:03:20,361
Who cries like this just
because their father-in-law is sick?

44
00:03:23,701 --> 00:03:25,131
I've never had...

45
00:03:27,031 --> 00:03:29,241
a mother or a father.

46
00:03:31,401 --> 00:03:32,471
To me...

47
00:03:33,871 --> 00:03:36,081
he was the only parent I ever had.

48
00:03:36,541 --> 00:03:38,441
(Admissions, Radiology,
Nuclear Medicine)

49
00:03:43,421 --> 00:03:46,021
You brought my father-in-law
to the hospital...

50
00:03:46,121 --> 00:03:47,891
when he collapsed, didn't you?

51
00:03:49,561 --> 00:03:50,561
Yes.

52
00:03:51,391 --> 00:03:52,761
Thank you so much.

53
00:03:53,761 --> 00:03:55,931
When I think about him collapsing
on the street all alone,

54
00:03:57,161 --> 00:03:59,201
my heart breaks.

55
00:04:01,401 --> 00:04:02,601
I'll repay you.

56
00:04:04,671 --> 00:04:05,911
As long as I live,

57
00:04:06,841 --> 00:04:08,341
I'll spend my life repaying you.

58
00:04:10,281 --> 00:04:11,341
Excuse me?

59
00:04:12,181 --> 00:04:13,311
About my Hyun Bin...

60
00:04:14,651 --> 00:04:16,481
I have no right
to oppose his marriage.

61
00:04:18,021 --> 00:04:20,791
He's not my biological son,
so how could I stop him?

62
00:04:22,361 --> 00:04:23,991
I was just being difficult.

63
00:04:27,891 --> 00:04:30,531
Get married. To my Hyun Bin.

64
00:04:32,901 --> 00:04:34,901
As for the doctor...

65
00:04:36,701 --> 00:04:38,041
I'll apologize...

66
00:04:38,341 --> 00:04:40,271
and do whatever it takes
to get her permission.

67
00:04:47,781 --> 00:04:49,081
Thank you.

68
00:04:59,331 --> 00:05:01,361
Seriously? What are you doing?

69
00:05:06,601 --> 00:05:09,141
Hey, what is all this?

70
00:05:09,741 --> 00:05:10,771
I...

71
00:05:12,511 --> 00:05:15,011
I know very well you don't
approve of me, Dr. Han.

72
00:05:16,311 --> 00:05:19,251
Get up first.
Let's talk standing up. Okay?

73
00:05:19,351 --> 00:05:22,751
I truly, sincerely apologize.

74
00:05:23,121 --> 00:05:27,351
I get it, so please get up.
Hurry, please.

75
00:05:30,891 --> 00:05:32,361
For everything I've done...

76
00:05:32,961 --> 00:05:34,891
the hurt I've caused you, Dr. Han,

77
00:05:35,861 --> 00:05:39,271
and my reckless behavior,
I'm truly ashamed.

78
00:05:39,901 --> 00:05:41,201
But if you could just once,

79
00:05:41,701 --> 00:05:43,671
if you could forgive
my past mistakes...

80
00:05:43,741 --> 00:05:45,301
I swear to you...

81
00:05:45,371 --> 00:05:47,211
I'll be so good to you and Ju Ah.

82
00:05:49,241 --> 00:05:50,781
I'm begging you, Dr. Han.

83
00:05:52,011 --> 00:05:54,751
Please give the kids
your blessing to marry.

84
00:05:57,251 --> 00:05:58,381
What? Not long ago,

85
00:05:58,451 --> 00:06:00,891
you were adamantly
asking me to stop them,

86
00:06:01,091 --> 00:06:03,921
saying Ju Ah was hitting on him
and threatening to pull her hair.

87
00:06:04,161 --> 00:06:06,831
Why the sudden change of heart?

88
00:06:06,891 --> 00:06:09,201
I was truly thoughtless
and disrespectful.

89
00:06:09,601 --> 00:06:10,961
I'm so sorry.

90
00:06:11,461 --> 00:06:14,431
I want to know why
you changed your mind.

91
00:06:17,201 --> 00:06:18,471
Perhaps this is...

92
00:06:20,511 --> 00:06:21,711
my father-in-law's...

93
00:06:22,381 --> 00:06:24,781
last wish.

94
00:06:25,811 --> 00:06:26,811
What?

95
00:06:27,751 --> 00:06:28,951
My father-in-law...

96
00:06:30,151 --> 00:06:32,081
didn't go on a trip.

97
00:06:32,721 --> 00:06:35,191
He secretly checked himself
into the hospital alone,

98
00:06:35,821 --> 00:06:38,561
- and he's receiving chemotherapy.
- What?

99
00:06:39,891 --> 00:06:41,231
Chemotherapy?

100
00:06:43,401 --> 00:06:44,661
My father-in-law...

101
00:06:45,871 --> 00:06:48,701
has acute leukemia.

102
00:06:49,241 --> 00:06:50,241
Oh my.

103
00:06:52,641 --> 00:06:55,541
That must be why, despite
the double in-laws situation,

104
00:06:55,611 --> 00:06:57,181
he wanted to rush the wedding,

105
00:06:57,681 --> 00:07:00,781
and why he was shouting at me.

106
00:07:01,311 --> 00:07:02,321
Dr. Han.

107
00:07:03,151 --> 00:07:08,091
Please. Please give your blessing
for their marriage.

108
00:07:09,061 --> 00:07:12,461
Please, Dr. Han.
Oh, what am I going to do?

109
00:07:12,891 --> 00:07:14,991
I was so wrong.

110
00:07:15,731 --> 00:07:17,161
Excuse me...

111
00:07:31,681 --> 00:07:33,381
Hey, so this is
the volunteer work you do...

112
00:07:33,451 --> 00:07:35,111
- after you're done for the day.
- Yes.

113
00:07:35,111 --> 00:07:39,091
Even if the kids call it childish,
singing makes him happy.

114
00:07:41,691 --> 00:07:42,691
What?

115
00:07:42,691 --> 00:07:44,861
Coming here has made me feel
so much better.

116
00:07:44,921 --> 00:07:46,261
- Right?
- Ju Ah...

117
00:07:46,531 --> 00:07:47,761
That's right.

118
00:07:48,661 --> 00:07:51,861
There are a lot
of people in this lobby.

119
00:07:53,831 --> 00:07:54,931
(Guardian Waiting Room)

120
00:07:55,471 --> 00:07:56,471
Father...

121
00:08:05,311 --> 00:08:09,251
Grandfather, should we head back in?
The nurse will be looking for you.

122
00:08:09,421 --> 00:08:11,051
Yes, all right.

123
00:08:11,781 --> 00:08:12,791
Let's go.

124
00:08:16,821 --> 00:08:19,491
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I can walk.

125
00:08:34,411 --> 00:08:35,671
I'm sorry.

126
00:08:36,211 --> 00:08:40,381
Grandfather insisted that
I not tell his family.

127
00:08:41,251 --> 00:08:45,421
But just a little while ago,
your wife was here.

128
00:08:47,121 --> 00:08:48,121
Se Ri was?

129
00:08:51,221 --> 00:08:52,221
My father...

130
00:08:53,261 --> 00:08:55,061
How long does he have?

131
00:09:00,101 --> 00:09:01,101
It's okay.

132
00:09:01,971 --> 00:09:03,241
Tell me honestly.

133
00:09:04,241 --> 00:09:06,271
A bone marrow transplant
will be difficult.

134
00:09:06,611 --> 00:09:09,611
They recommended
maintenance chemotherapy, right?

135
00:09:09,881 --> 00:09:10,881
Yes.

136
00:09:11,411 --> 00:09:12,411
It's different for everyone.

137
00:09:12,481 --> 00:09:14,081
If he maintains a positive outlook
on his treatment,

138
00:09:14,151 --> 00:09:16,181
he'll have a good outcome.

139
00:09:21,451 --> 00:09:22,591
Stay strong.

140
00:09:30,101 --> 00:09:31,831
If my father passes away too,

141
00:09:32,531 --> 00:09:34,131
what am I going to do, honey?

142
00:09:34,901 --> 00:09:36,341
Honey.

143
00:09:37,071 --> 00:09:38,901
If I can't even take care
of my own parents,

144
00:09:38,901 --> 00:09:40,671
how can I be in politics?

145
00:09:41,341 --> 00:09:43,611
I think I'm just going to quit
the race and everything.

146
00:09:44,181 --> 00:09:48,751
No. Don't think that way.
Do what Grandfather wants.

147
00:09:48,811 --> 00:09:50,351
He said it was his wish.

148
00:09:50,821 --> 00:09:53,791
You've been taking care
of him this whole time?

149
00:09:56,561 --> 00:09:59,261
Dr. Gong and Ms. Na stopped by.

150
00:09:59,531 --> 00:10:01,591
And Ju Ah has been visiting often,
it seems.

151
00:10:02,901 --> 00:10:04,431
Oh my gosh.

152
00:10:05,631 --> 00:10:07,971
Honey. Today I...

153
00:10:08,631 --> 00:10:11,471
I went to Dr. Han
and begged her on my knees.

154
00:10:12,001 --> 00:10:13,011
What?

155
00:10:13,571 --> 00:10:14,571
Why?

156
00:10:14,971 --> 00:10:16,411
Hyun Bin and Ju Ah...

157
00:10:16,911 --> 00:10:19,151
I asked her to let them get married.

158
00:10:27,891 --> 00:10:28,891
So...

159
00:10:29,521 --> 00:10:30,661
did you give them your blessing?

160
00:10:31,261 --> 00:10:35,031
No. I asked
for some time to think about it.

161
00:10:36,561 --> 00:10:37,561
I see.

162
00:10:38,531 --> 00:10:42,331
Mother, you knew Mr. Yang was ill,
did you not?

163
00:10:42,741 --> 00:10:45,941
I happened to find out.

164
00:10:46,541 --> 00:10:50,781
I know the situation is urgent,
and I feel for them,

165
00:10:51,281 --> 00:10:53,381
but marriage is one of the most
important events in life.

166
00:10:53,751 --> 00:10:56,181
It should not be a decision made
out of sacrifice.

167
00:10:57,681 --> 00:11:00,891
It is not a sacrifice.
It is consideration.

168
00:11:01,751 --> 00:11:05,321
It means she loves Hyun Bin
that much.

169
00:11:06,591 --> 00:11:08,161
Was I being too harsh?

170
00:11:08,491 --> 00:11:10,301
No.

171
00:11:10,831 --> 00:11:13,371
I am sick myself,
so I must seem awful...

172
00:11:13,431 --> 00:11:15,431
for being so practical, right?

173
00:11:17,971 --> 00:11:19,871
From Ju Ah's point of view,

174
00:11:20,171 --> 00:11:22,171
it is right
for you to think that way.

175
00:11:22,781 --> 00:11:23,911
That is what it means
to be a mother.

176
00:11:31,251 --> 00:11:32,951
Mom, why are you here?

177
00:11:33,621 --> 00:11:36,721
- Let's talk.
- What?

178
00:11:43,031 --> 00:11:44,031
Gong Ju Ah.

179
00:11:45,161 --> 00:11:47,131
Think this through carefully.

180
00:11:48,331 --> 00:11:49,341
Okay.

181
00:11:49,601 --> 00:11:52,141
Other people's circumstances
are not what is important.

182
00:11:52,741 --> 00:11:53,741
I know.

183
00:11:54,271 --> 00:11:58,911
I actually made a list of the pros
and cons of marrying Hyun Bin.

184
00:11:59,551 --> 00:12:02,411
As I was writing, I realized
there were quite a few cons.

185
00:12:02,851 --> 00:12:06,251
But there was only one pro.

186
00:12:06,721 --> 00:12:08,221
What was the pro?

187
00:12:08,851 --> 00:12:09,861
Hyun Bin.

188
00:12:10,221 --> 00:12:11,661
Good grief.

189
00:12:13,161 --> 00:12:16,701
His name alone outweighed
all of the cons.

190
00:12:18,361 --> 00:12:22,171
Besides, our family
is overflowing with love these days.

191
00:12:22,401 --> 00:12:24,471
Grandma and Grandfather,

192
00:12:24,671 --> 00:12:27,711
Mom and Dad, Uncle and Aunt.

193
00:12:28,811 --> 00:12:32,411
When we wake up,
we ask each other if we slept well.

194
00:12:32,481 --> 00:12:35,611
We check on each other's feelings
and share delicious food.

195
00:12:36,551 --> 00:12:39,491
You all smile whenever
your eyes meet.

196
00:12:40,221 --> 00:12:44,721
I want to live like that too.
With Hyun Bin.

197
00:12:46,091 --> 00:12:50,161
Hyun Bin's mother?
I can handle her. Do not worry.

198
00:12:50,601 --> 00:12:54,031
- I am your daughter, am I not?
- Only when it suits you, right?

199
00:13:00,211 --> 00:13:01,541
Here, Ji Hu, have some.

200
00:13:01,871 --> 00:13:03,311
You should have some too, Aunt.

201
00:13:03,611 --> 00:13:04,681
Okay, I will.

202
00:13:05,981 --> 00:13:09,321
- Honey, I am just stepping out...
- Where are you going at this hour?

203
00:13:09,651 --> 00:13:12,451
To get some fresh air...

204
00:13:13,121 --> 00:13:15,691
- Oh my.
- Why?

205
00:13:16,521 --> 00:13:17,691
Hello, Dr. Han.

206
00:13:18,861 --> 00:13:21,391
To what do I owe the call?

207
00:13:22,291 --> 00:13:24,461
No, it is not too late.
It is all right.

208
00:13:25,101 --> 00:13:27,001
So that you could rest easy,

209
00:13:27,531 --> 00:13:30,141
I called even though
I knew how late it was.

210
00:13:30,841 --> 00:13:34,711
- Does that mean...
- Yes.

211
00:13:36,211 --> 00:13:37,541
Their marriage...

212
00:13:39,651 --> 00:13:41,311
I will give my permission.

213
00:13:43,781 --> 00:13:47,451
Thank you, Dr. Han.
Really, thank you.

214
00:13:48,251 --> 00:13:51,861
I do not know
what others may think of my Ju Ah,

215
00:13:52,561 --> 00:13:56,961
but to me,
she is my greatest pride and joy.

216
00:13:57,931 --> 00:14:01,171
Of course. I know.

217
00:14:02,231 --> 00:14:06,111
Please take good care of her.

218
00:14:07,541 --> 00:14:11,381
Yes, Dr. Han.
Thank you so much. Thank you.

219
00:14:11,741 --> 00:14:13,681
Yes. Yes, goodbye.

220
00:14:15,151 --> 00:14:17,981
Did Seong Mi approve the marriage?

221
00:14:19,081 --> 00:14:20,321
Yes, honey.

222
00:14:20,591 --> 00:14:21,591
That is great.

223
00:14:22,861 --> 00:14:25,561
Are Hyun Bin
and Ju Ah getting married?

224
00:14:25,861 --> 00:14:29,031
I can see why
this would be confusing for Ji Hu.

225
00:14:29,361 --> 00:14:30,831
That's how it turned out.

226
00:14:31,131 --> 00:14:33,301
Yes, right.

227
00:14:37,241 --> 00:14:38,301
Oh, so that's what happened.

228
00:14:40,771 --> 00:14:42,781
What will I do about
my father-in-law?

229
00:14:45,711 --> 00:14:47,681
All right.

230
00:14:48,211 --> 00:14:49,211
What did you say?

231
00:14:50,021 --> 00:14:51,021
Really?

232
00:14:52,151 --> 00:14:54,991
Okay, I'm hanging up. Bye.

233
00:14:58,721 --> 00:15:01,061
Why? Did my sister-in-law
come and make a scene again?

234
00:15:01,331 --> 00:15:03,801
No. She came to ask permission...

235
00:15:03,861 --> 00:15:05,861
for Hyun Bin and Ju Ah to marry,

236
00:15:06,831 --> 00:15:07,901
and she got down on her knees.

237
00:15:08,601 --> 00:15:11,101
Oh my gosh, really?
So did she agree to the marriage?

238
00:15:13,541 --> 00:15:14,571
Yes.

239
00:15:14,741 --> 00:15:16,041
Oh my, that's wonderful.

240
00:15:32,091 --> 00:15:34,661
Eun Bin,
I'm afraid I have some bad news.

241
00:15:35,491 --> 00:15:38,331
Hyun Bin got permission
to get married.

242
00:16:00,451 --> 00:16:01,951
I guess we should give up, right?

243
00:16:03,121 --> 00:16:04,121
I guess so.

244
00:16:04,921 --> 00:16:07,131
Becoming double in-laws
was already this hard...

245
00:16:08,561 --> 00:16:10,561
It's never going to work for us.

246
00:16:15,171 --> 00:16:17,301
- Eun Bin.
- Yes?

247
00:16:18,441 --> 00:16:20,611
I'm so sorry.

248
00:16:21,911 --> 00:16:24,181
Why are you sorry?

249
00:16:26,911 --> 00:16:29,821
If I had known,
I would have treated you better.

250
00:16:31,921 --> 00:16:33,591
- Back when you liked me...
- What was it?

251
00:16:33,821 --> 00:16:35,221
- I should've cherished you...
- As you supported me...

252
00:16:35,251 --> 00:16:36,261
I should have been
more affectionate.

253
00:16:36,361 --> 00:16:38,961
To her boyfriend who was studying
for an exam.

254
00:16:39,091 --> 00:16:40,731
- Hey.
- Why are you here?

255
00:16:40,791 --> 00:16:41,861
I came to see you, of course.

256
00:16:41,931 --> 00:16:44,061
I took you being by my side
for granted,

257
00:16:44,961 --> 00:16:47,571
so I didn't treasure your feelings.

258
00:16:58,441 --> 00:17:00,051
Looks like Yang Eun Bin
has made it big.

259
00:17:00,881 --> 00:17:02,921
I never thought I'd hear you say
something like that.

260
00:17:06,921 --> 00:17:08,991
Still, if anything happens,
be sure to call me.

261
00:17:11,221 --> 00:17:13,091
Like if I get roped
into a pyramid scheme...

262
00:17:13,161 --> 00:17:14,531
or splashed with dirty water?

263
00:17:23,441 --> 00:17:24,871
Take care of yourself.

264
00:17:26,311 --> 00:17:28,271
Make sure you achieve your dream.

265
00:17:29,171 --> 00:17:30,211
Okay?

266
00:17:35,351 --> 00:17:36,351
You too.

267
00:17:37,781 --> 00:17:40,051
You have to become the best stylist
in the country.

268
00:17:40,891 --> 00:17:41,991
I'll be rooting for you.

269
00:17:44,691 --> 00:17:45,691
Okay.

270
00:17:46,591 --> 00:17:48,361
Let's root for each other.

271
00:18:48,091 --> 00:18:49,121
I'm home.

272
00:18:51,921 --> 00:18:52,921
Honey,

273
00:18:54,331 --> 00:18:55,731
why are you so late?

274
00:18:56,431 --> 00:18:57,431
Sorry.

275
00:18:58,831 --> 00:19:00,031
Have you been drinking?

276
00:19:01,171 --> 00:19:02,231
No.

277
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:04,271
Did you by any chance...

278
00:19:05,941 --> 00:19:07,641
go see Father?

279
00:19:14,251 --> 00:19:15,411
Oh no.

280
00:19:16,151 --> 00:19:17,151
Honey.

281
00:19:18,421 --> 00:19:20,851
It's okay.

282
00:19:24,491 --> 00:19:25,491
It's okay.

283
00:19:32,801 --> 00:19:35,701
- Look at the pretty people here.
- Father.

284
00:19:37,001 --> 00:19:39,941
My, why such a feast so early
in the morning?

285
00:19:40,371 --> 00:19:43,341
Father, would you mind tasting
the seasoning on the vegetables?

286
00:19:43,511 --> 00:19:46,411
- Should I? Here, just a moment.
- Okay.

287
00:19:46,481 --> 00:19:47,481
Here you go.

288
00:19:48,451 --> 00:19:49,981
How is it?
Does it need more seasoning?

289
00:19:50,921 --> 00:19:51,921
It's delicious.

290
00:19:52,551 --> 00:19:54,221
Wow, this is really good.

291
00:19:54,851 --> 00:19:58,221
How can my eldest daughter-in-law
be so good at everything?

292
00:19:59,931 --> 00:20:01,131
Oh, you're too kind.

293
00:20:02,531 --> 00:20:03,801
But Father,

294
00:20:04,701 --> 00:20:07,231
did you hear
that Ju Ah decided to get married?

295
00:20:07,301 --> 00:20:09,171
He knows. I told him.

296
00:20:10,071 --> 00:20:11,971
Second Cutie,
you're not just forcing yourself...

297
00:20:12,041 --> 00:20:15,241
- to be okay with this, are you?
- No, of course not.

298
00:20:15,971 --> 00:20:18,641
And will our Cutie Youngest be okay?

299
00:20:19,641 --> 00:20:22,411
Wait,
is Cutie Youngest the right term?

300
00:20:23,181 --> 00:20:25,581
She's also the groom's aunt.

301
00:20:26,491 --> 00:20:28,191
I know. Gosh, it's so complicated.

302
00:20:28,791 --> 00:20:31,691
But why are they rushing
the wedding?

303
00:20:31,961 --> 00:20:33,091
They could have taken their time.

304
00:20:34,431 --> 00:20:35,661
They said they want...

305
00:20:35,731 --> 00:20:37,601
to live together as soon
as possible.

306
00:20:37,801 --> 00:20:39,701
They said they're jealous
because we're all so lovey-dovey.

307
00:20:40,801 --> 00:20:42,331
Oh, but still.

308
00:20:42,871 --> 00:20:43,871
What?

309
00:20:44,841 --> 00:20:46,171
Oh my, so early in the morning.

310
00:20:48,541 --> 00:20:50,511
What is it, Se Ri? What's wrong?

311
00:20:52,141 --> 00:20:53,881
Shouldn't we tell her?

312
00:20:54,551 --> 00:20:56,751
That's something Seon Chul
should handle himself.

313
00:20:57,451 --> 00:20:59,251
It's not our place to say anything.

314
00:21:04,091 --> 00:21:06,691
I wanted to know when Dr. Han
is going to the hospital.

315
00:21:07,491 --> 00:21:10,301
It's a little awkward
for me to ask her myself.

316
00:21:10,661 --> 00:21:14,031
Could you ask him
and text me the details? Okay?

317
00:21:16,201 --> 00:21:18,171
Why do you need Dr. Han's schedule?

318
00:21:18,641 --> 00:21:21,071
Oh, it's just for something.

319
00:21:21,311 --> 00:21:24,211
By the way, are you sure
you don't need my help...

320
00:21:24,281 --> 00:21:25,481
with the election?

321
00:21:26,211 --> 00:21:28,681
Jeong Han is helping me out
as if it's his own campaign.

322
00:21:29,281 --> 00:21:32,921
Honey, I'm going to work
really hard this time...

323
00:21:33,351 --> 00:21:35,991
and get that city council badge
to show Father.

324
00:21:40,961 --> 00:21:43,861
We got all the signatures
for Dong Ik's candidate nomination.

325
00:21:45,301 --> 00:21:47,331
Good, I'm glad you got them all
before it was too late.

326
00:21:47,401 --> 00:21:50,801
- You did well.
- Oh, I hardly did anything.

327
00:21:51,241 --> 00:21:52,501
It was all thanks to Jeong Han.

328
00:21:52,771 --> 00:21:55,371
- You did it all.
- No, I didn't.

329
00:21:55,441 --> 00:21:59,041
My goodness,
look at you two being so chummy.

330
00:21:59,281 --> 00:22:00,911
May you live happily ever after.

331
00:22:02,811 --> 00:22:05,021
I'm going to go see Seon Chul.

332
00:22:06,121 --> 00:22:08,391
Oh, I should be the one going.
I'm sorry.

333
00:22:08,921 --> 00:22:12,621
Father, shouldn't we tell
Dong Suk, too?

334
00:22:12,891 --> 00:22:16,291
No. He said he can't stand
his children getting involved.

335
00:22:16,761 --> 00:22:17,761
Right now, the priority is...

336
00:22:17,831 --> 00:22:19,331
for him to get his treatment
in peace.

337
00:22:19,701 --> 00:22:21,501
- Let's just do what he wants.
- Yes.

338
00:22:21,571 --> 00:22:22,571
- Right.
- Yes.

339
00:22:22,901 --> 00:22:25,671
I'll be the one in charge
of the hospital visits.

340
00:22:26,071 --> 00:22:29,071
Dong Ik, you think of your father
as being on a trip...

341
00:22:29,141 --> 00:22:30,811
and focus only on the election.

342
00:22:31,681 --> 00:22:32,741
I understand, Father.

343
00:22:33,011 --> 00:22:34,951
- Okay. I'm leaving.
- Yes.

344
00:22:35,211 --> 00:22:37,621
- Yes, take care, Father.
- Take care, Father. Yes.

345
00:22:39,381 --> 00:22:40,391
Oh, dear.

346
00:22:40,951 --> 00:22:41,951
Dae Han.

347
00:22:42,621 --> 00:22:43,861
You need to have a kid too.

348
00:22:44,921 --> 00:22:46,021
Dong Ik, I really...

349
00:22:46,491 --> 00:22:48,931
am truly, truly doing my best.

350
00:22:49,631 --> 00:22:52,701
All right.
Once the candidacy is registered,

351
00:22:52,701 --> 00:22:54,531
what comes next?

352
00:22:54,701 --> 00:22:57,301
- We need to promote.
- Promotion.

353
00:22:57,441 --> 00:22:59,641
I've been thinking...

354
00:23:00,341 --> 00:23:01,741
- about the promotion...
- Yes.

355
00:23:02,111 --> 00:23:04,411
Jeong Han,
could we maybe go with your concept?

356
00:23:04,911 --> 00:23:05,981
My concept?

357
00:23:06,541 --> 00:23:07,881
What is my concept?

358
00:23:14,691 --> 00:23:16,351
This one's good.

359
00:23:16,421 --> 00:23:19,561
This style suits your face better,
Dad.

360
00:23:19,691 --> 00:23:22,531
- Right? I like this one too.
- Really?

361
00:23:22,931 --> 00:23:27,801
What do you think?
My daughter's a top stylist.

362
00:23:27,901 --> 00:23:31,501
Wow, she is a total pro. A real pro.

363
00:23:32,341 --> 00:23:33,571
She really is. Yes.

364
00:23:34,211 --> 00:23:38,681
Call me anytime you need a stylist.

365
00:23:39,681 --> 00:23:41,311
Oh, impressive.

366
00:23:42,411 --> 00:23:47,151
Keep your bangs down a bit
like this to soften your look,

367
00:23:47,891 --> 00:23:49,961
roll up your sleeves slightly,

368
00:23:50,021 --> 00:23:51,921
and to give off that 'man
of the people...

369
00:23:51,991 --> 00:23:53,431
who gets things done' vibe...

370
00:23:53,861 --> 00:23:56,161
the styling is complete.
How do you like it?

371
00:23:57,561 --> 00:24:00,201
That's the best
you have ever looked.

372
00:24:00,731 --> 00:24:02,231
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

373
00:24:02,301 --> 00:24:04,141
Dong Ik,
you look like a different person.

374
00:24:04,771 --> 00:24:07,811
Wow, our Eun Bin has
the magic touch. Pure magic.

375
00:24:08,341 --> 00:24:12,841
Thanks. Who's taking the pictures?
I didn't prepare anything.

376
00:24:12,841 --> 00:24:15,751
We have an expert for that too.

377
00:24:16,981 --> 00:24:18,181
I'm here.

378
00:24:18,681 --> 00:24:21,351
Come in, our clever young in-law.

379
00:24:22,021 --> 00:24:25,561
Our Woo Jae here will take care of
everything, right up to the posters.

380
00:24:27,831 --> 00:24:28,961
Hey, Eun Bin.

381
00:24:29,361 --> 00:24:30,761
Hi.

382
00:24:31,461 --> 00:24:32,531
Woo Jae.

383
00:24:32,931 --> 00:24:33,931
Why are you waiting?
Let's go outside.

384
00:24:34,001 --> 00:24:36,101
We need to take these pictures.
Let's go, let's go.

385
00:24:37,341 --> 00:24:38,441
This is great, man.

386
00:24:49,211 --> 00:24:51,151
Hey, the shadow...

387
00:24:51,221 --> 00:24:52,351
just on this side here.

388
00:24:52,421 --> 00:24:54,421
- Dad, that's so old-fashioned.
- Seriously.

389
00:24:54,721 --> 00:24:55,751
Okay, good.

390
00:24:56,251 --> 00:24:58,721
- A little more natural, be natural.
- Try smiling.

391
00:24:58,991 --> 00:25:00,161
Come on.

392
00:25:05,101 --> 00:25:08,371
- Tilt your head a bit.
- Dad, that's old-fashioned.

393
00:25:09,071 --> 00:25:11,041
Let's lift this up a bit more
and this part...

394
00:25:13,041 --> 00:25:14,171
- Pro Yang.
- How's this?

395
00:25:14,241 --> 00:25:17,841
Pro Yang. Good.
You just need to do well.

396
00:25:18,681 --> 00:25:19,741
Okay, I'm taking the shot.

397
00:25:20,581 --> 00:25:22,381
One, two, three.

398
00:25:23,751 --> 00:25:25,521
Hello, Ms. Na, Dr. Han.

399
00:25:25,581 --> 00:25:27,721
Oh,
what brings you here at this hour?

400
00:25:28,221 --> 00:25:30,321
Ms. Na, please take this.

401
00:25:30,961 --> 00:25:32,761
What is this?

402
00:25:33,491 --> 00:25:35,631
It's a pledge promising I won't
be a difficult mother-in-law.

403
00:25:35,891 --> 00:25:38,701
For the happiness
of my future daughter-in-law, Ju Ah,

404
00:25:38,761 --> 00:25:40,431
it states that
I will never interfere...

405
00:25:40,501 --> 00:25:41,771
or make her do all the work.

406
00:25:41,831 --> 00:25:45,171
- I signed and added my thumbprint.
- Oh my.

407
00:25:47,141 --> 00:25:50,181
You see, I've never
been mistreated by my in-laws,

408
00:25:50,241 --> 00:25:52,181
and I enjoy housework so much
that even when...

409
00:25:52,181 --> 00:25:53,451
I lived with my sister-in-law,

410
00:25:53,511 --> 00:25:57,351
I never let her lift a finger.
So please, don't you worry.

411
00:25:57,421 --> 00:25:58,721
You can trust me.

412
00:25:59,881 --> 00:26:00,891
All right.

413
00:26:02,021 --> 00:26:03,491
Dr. Han,
you're on your way to the hospital,

414
00:26:03,561 --> 00:26:05,161
aren't you?
Please allow me to give you a ride.

415
00:26:05,221 --> 00:26:06,961
That's all right.

416
00:26:07,031 --> 00:26:10,361
Go with me.
I made time just for this.

417
00:26:10,431 --> 00:26:14,871
We already gave you our blessing.
You don't have to do all this.

418
00:26:14,931 --> 00:26:17,771
Come on. Let's go.
I will see you next time.

419
00:26:17,841 --> 00:26:18,901
- No, really...
- Goodbye.

420
00:26:18,971 --> 00:26:20,341
- I'm really fine.
- Let's go, let's go.

421
00:26:20,411 --> 00:26:21,411
Oh my goodness.

422
00:26:24,481 --> 00:26:27,281
The press coverage
of the event has been positive.

423
00:26:28,381 --> 00:26:31,051
Good work, everyone.
Our very first event...

424
00:26:31,121 --> 00:26:32,751
was a significant success.

425
00:26:33,051 --> 00:26:36,391
Thanks to Lee Yoon Seo's appearance
on that entertainment show,

426
00:26:36,451 --> 00:26:37,691
Pelliv sales have skyrocketed.

427
00:26:39,091 --> 00:26:42,531
Perfect.
All right, for the next meeting,

428
00:26:42,591 --> 00:26:45,901
each of you, come up with a concept
for the pop-up store. That's all.

429
00:26:48,501 --> 00:26:49,501
I mean...

430
00:26:50,441 --> 00:26:53,811
Please, can we all please focus
on the meeting?

431
00:26:54,041 --> 00:26:57,241
From now on,
the CEO is banned from our meetings.

432
00:26:57,381 --> 00:27:00,881
Every time you show up,
the team can't focus.

433
00:27:01,811 --> 00:27:03,381
All right,
shall we start our meeting?

434
00:27:07,421 --> 00:27:08,521
What's the concept
for the wedding attire?

435
00:27:08,591 --> 00:27:10,161
Since they're having
a small wedding,

436
00:27:10,221 --> 00:27:11,621
instead of something too flashy,

437
00:27:11,721 --> 00:27:14,091
I think a simple
yet elegant design would be best.

438
00:27:14,291 --> 00:27:16,931
Then let's go with an A-line
for a slim silhouette.

439
00:27:17,001 --> 00:27:19,031
I'll look into materials that allow
for easy movement.

440
00:27:19,261 --> 00:27:22,431
Excuse me, what is everyone doing?

441
00:27:22,571 --> 00:27:25,371
I think the groom's entrance
should be more impactful.

442
00:27:25,441 --> 00:27:28,671
To capture the passion of Argentina,
maybe we can play some tango music?

443
00:27:28,741 --> 00:27:31,181
The groom can dance the tango
as he makes his entrance.

444
00:27:32,281 --> 00:27:34,981
Are you talking about me?
You want me to dance?

445
00:27:35,511 --> 00:27:36,881
You two
can just go about your business.

446
00:27:37,151 --> 00:27:40,891
- Why are you planning our wedding?
- Gosh, please.

447
00:27:41,821 --> 00:27:43,621
I've always dreamed of being
a wedding planner.

448
00:27:43,691 --> 00:27:46,161
Let me do this. Please.

449
00:27:53,061 --> 00:27:56,031
Hey. Your daughter-in-law
came to see Seong Mi.

450
00:27:56,101 --> 00:27:58,571
She smoothed things over with her
and apologized.

451
00:27:59,501 --> 00:28:01,271
See? She listens to me.

452
00:28:02,171 --> 00:28:05,141
Se Ri thinks of me
as her own father.

453
00:28:06,241 --> 00:28:10,111
Her only problem is
that she speaks before she thinks.

454
00:28:10,621 --> 00:28:13,451
She has a good heart
and she's very loyal.

455
00:28:14,691 --> 00:28:16,891
Well, my eldest daughter-in-law...

456
00:28:17,161 --> 00:28:19,821
She can read people like a book.

457
00:28:19,961 --> 00:28:23,191
She's unbelievably smart and wise.

458
00:28:23,361 --> 00:28:27,731
She may seem cold and stern,
but she's very understanding...

459
00:28:27,801 --> 00:28:29,471
and doesn't hold grudges.

460
00:28:30,441 --> 00:28:33,041
We both lucked out
with our daughters-in-law.

461
00:28:36,171 --> 00:28:38,941
How can a cancer patient be
this feisty?

462
00:28:40,681 --> 00:28:41,911
My hand is trembling.

463
00:28:49,721 --> 00:28:51,521
Dr. Han, you feel nauseous,
don't you?

464
00:28:51,591 --> 00:28:54,361
I bought some water for you,
so have a sip.

465
00:28:55,191 --> 00:28:56,361
Thank you.

466
00:29:01,371 --> 00:29:02,931
Should I turn up the AC?

467
00:29:03,701 --> 00:29:05,141
Oh, it's fine.

468
00:29:08,971 --> 00:29:12,041
I told you I wanted to leave
by myself. Why did you wait?

469
00:29:12,041 --> 00:29:13,541
You have work to do.

470
00:29:13,611 --> 00:29:16,351
My employees are watching the store,
so it's fine.

471
00:29:16,411 --> 00:29:20,351
Anyway,
please don't come with me next time.

472
00:29:20,951 --> 00:29:21,951
Oh, why not?

473
00:29:22,021 --> 00:29:25,391
Are you embarrassed
for me to see you when you're sick?

474
00:29:25,691 --> 00:29:28,331
I'm not embarrassed.
It's just that it's a burden.

475
00:29:28,631 --> 00:29:32,001
Why would you feel that way?
We're family now.

476
00:29:32,101 --> 00:29:34,171
Strictly speaking, we're in-laws.

477
00:29:34,231 --> 00:29:36,771
Not just in-laws.
We're double in-laws.

478
00:29:37,441 --> 00:29:41,911
This is no ordinary connection.
This is our destiny.

479
00:29:45,481 --> 00:29:47,151
This is so exhausting.

480
00:29:55,991 --> 00:29:58,361
Oh my. I'm sorry to put you
through all this trouble.

481
00:29:58,421 --> 00:30:00,191
Oh, it's no trouble at all.

482
00:30:00,331 --> 00:30:01,591
(Tomatoes)

483
00:30:02,231 --> 00:30:04,361
So I should load all
of this in here?

484
00:30:05,001 --> 00:30:08,001
Yes.
You can just load it right here.

485
00:30:08,931 --> 00:30:13,141
- Thank you.
- Not at all. Tomorrow,

486
00:30:13,201 --> 00:30:15,511
I'll bring a cooler and other supplies
for the heat wave.

487
00:30:15,571 --> 00:30:17,381
Oh my goodness.

488
00:30:20,751 --> 00:30:24,581
Oh, really? Okay, yes. Thank you.
Yes, yes, I understand.

489
00:30:26,551 --> 00:30:28,751
- Dong Ik.
- Yes?

490
00:30:28,821 --> 00:30:30,921
The poll results are in.

491
00:30:32,161 --> 00:30:33,291
What's the percentage?

492
00:30:33,761 --> 00:30:38,031
The number's similar.
It's a three...

493
00:30:38,101 --> 00:30:42,031
- Is it 0.3 percent again?
- Yes, but...

494
00:30:42,501 --> 00:30:45,001
There's no zero. It's three percent.

495
00:30:45,071 --> 00:30:46,671
- What? Really?
- Yes.

496
00:30:46,741 --> 00:30:49,211
- Wow, it went up tenfold?
- It's ten times higher. Ten times.

497
00:30:49,271 --> 00:30:52,281
- Yes.
- We can hit 30 percent, Dong Ik.

498
00:30:52,541 --> 00:30:53,581
Let's do it.

499
00:30:53,581 --> 00:30:57,321
Let's do it, let's really do it.
I told you you had good energy.

500
00:30:57,751 --> 00:30:59,681
- Wow, three percent.
- Unbelievable.

501
00:30:59,751 --> 00:31:01,821
- Thanks, man.
- You know it.

502
00:31:08,631 --> 00:31:09,631
Tamin.

503
00:31:10,431 --> 00:31:13,401
- My gosh, be quiet.
- What are you doing?

504
00:31:13,801 --> 00:31:14,801
What is all this?

505
00:31:15,431 --> 00:31:18,401
Roasted garlic, seasoned chives,
and oyster pancakes.

506
00:31:19,241 --> 00:31:23,371
- You're eating all this now?
- Yes, it improves circulation...

507
00:31:23,641 --> 00:31:25,381
and helps with sperm motility.

508
00:31:26,441 --> 00:31:30,251
Oh, I'm getting desperate.
The pressure is immense.

509
00:31:30,421 --> 00:31:33,721
- Oh, Tamin.
- Just wait. It's almost ready.

510
00:31:36,621 --> 00:31:37,761
Oyster pancakes.

511
00:31:39,091 --> 00:31:40,191
Want to try one?

512
00:31:41,691 --> 00:31:42,791
You want to do what?

513
00:31:43,361 --> 00:31:48,171
- What, you don't want to?
- No, go on. Let's hear it.

514
00:31:51,341 --> 00:31:54,611
Okay, then. We will now establish
the rules of our marriage.

515
00:31:54,671 --> 00:31:56,771
First,
finances and asset management.

516
00:31:56,841 --> 00:31:58,281
We'll manage our own salaries...

517
00:31:58,341 --> 00:32:00,241
and chip in
for shared living expenses.

518
00:32:00,481 --> 00:32:04,221
- Please don't interrupt me.
- What? Go on.

519
00:32:04,751 --> 00:32:06,251
All income will be pooled
as a joint asset,

520
00:32:06,321 --> 00:32:07,321
and I will manage it.

521
00:32:07,391 --> 00:32:09,691
As for monthly expenses,
you'll submit a plan for approval.

522
00:32:09,751 --> 00:32:11,421
Hey, that's a bit...

523
00:32:11,491 --> 00:32:13,691
Don't talk back. Did we agree that
I get to decide or not?

524
00:32:13,761 --> 00:32:14,761
We did.

525
00:32:15,861 --> 00:32:17,261
Second, division of household labor.

526
00:32:17,331 --> 00:32:18,801
We'll alternate cooking
every other day...

527
00:32:18,861 --> 00:32:20,831
and take turns cleaning once a week.

528
00:32:21,531 --> 00:32:22,771
Once a week? That's ridiculous.

529
00:32:22,831 --> 00:32:24,401
The house needs
to be cleaned every day.

530
00:32:24,471 --> 00:32:26,601
Then whoever wants it cleaned
every day can do it.

531
00:32:27,041 --> 00:32:28,941
I'm not that concerned
with cleanliness.

532
00:32:29,641 --> 00:32:33,241
Oh, and no nagging if you find one
of my old socks under the bed.

533
00:32:35,281 --> 00:32:37,621
Why?
Do you want to call off the wedding?

534
00:32:38,021 --> 00:32:40,521
No. Go on. Keep going.

535
00:32:40,591 --> 00:32:43,221
Let me hear the rest before I decide
whether to call off the wedding.

536
00:32:44,161 --> 00:32:46,721
Next, we need to coordinate
our weekend plans.

537
00:32:46,761 --> 00:32:48,491
Is there anything to coordinate?

538
00:32:49,061 --> 00:32:51,361
Of course we'll be
together every moment.

539
00:32:52,331 --> 00:32:54,371
For a healthy marriage,
we'll each get...

540
00:32:54,431 --> 00:32:56,701
our own personal time
every other Saturday.

541
00:32:56,771 --> 00:32:59,271
Okay, fine.
What about our plan for kids?

542
00:32:59,341 --> 00:33:01,671
- One kid? Two?
- What are you talking about?

543
00:33:01,741 --> 00:33:04,041
- Three?
- Three? Are you kidding?

544
00:33:04,111 --> 00:33:06,441
We have to decide
if we'll have any at all.

545
00:33:06,541 --> 00:33:09,381
What? You said before
that if we have kids,

546
00:33:09,451 --> 00:33:12,921
we'd name them Ju Hyun and Ah Bin,
using parts of our names.

547
00:33:12,981 --> 00:33:15,621
You can say anything
during the honeymoon phase.

548
00:33:16,251 --> 00:33:18,861
Depending on the situation,
I'm open to being a DINK couple..

549
00:33:18,921 --> 00:33:20,591
Hey, being a DINK couple
is not an option.

550
00:33:20,631 --> 00:33:22,531
We're definitely having kids.
Got it?

551
00:33:22,591 --> 00:33:24,101
I'll be in charge of raising them.

552
00:33:25,101 --> 00:33:28,131
In that case,
let's decide on that later.

553
00:33:28,801 --> 00:33:30,871
- Is that all?
- That's all.

554
00:33:31,171 --> 00:33:32,941
I'm sleeping here tonight.

555
00:33:33,541 --> 00:33:36,471
Gosh. Forget it.
Go sleep at your place.

556
00:33:37,641 --> 00:33:39,911
Are you tired of me already?

557
00:33:40,111 --> 00:33:42,951
No, hey.
Our wedding is only a few days away,

558
00:33:43,011 --> 00:33:44,751
so you should spend time
with your family.

559
00:33:45,421 --> 00:33:46,481
Do you really mean that?

560
00:33:46,751 --> 00:33:47,751
No.

561
00:33:51,261 --> 00:33:52,291
Father, here you go.

562
00:33:54,761 --> 00:33:55,761
Yes.

563
00:34:00,161 --> 00:34:02,571
Father, he's been...

564
00:34:02,901 --> 00:34:06,141
working very hard
to grant your wish.

565
00:34:06,541 --> 00:34:10,041
- Is that so?
- Yes. And Ju Ah is doing well, too.

566
00:34:11,211 --> 00:34:12,781
I told Dong Suk...

567
00:34:13,081 --> 00:34:15,481
that I'll be back
for Hyun Bin's wedding.

568
00:34:16,281 --> 00:34:17,281
Okay.

569
00:34:19,581 --> 00:34:21,691
- Yes, go on in.
- Oh, dear.

570
00:34:21,851 --> 00:34:23,321
- Oh...
- I'm back, my friend.

571
00:34:23,391 --> 00:34:26,321
- Oh, you're here.
- Yes, welcome.

572
00:34:26,391 --> 00:34:27,391
Yes.

573
00:34:29,231 --> 00:34:31,501
- Grandfather.
- We're here.

574
00:34:31,761 --> 00:34:34,271
I thought you had the family
meeting today. Why are you here?

575
00:34:34,571 --> 00:34:38,071
Well, Ju Ah insisted that
we come and greet you first,

576
00:34:38,141 --> 00:34:39,141
Grandfather.

577
00:34:40,071 --> 00:34:42,311
So that you won't have to worry,
Grandfather,

578
00:34:42,441 --> 00:34:44,881
we'll live a happy life together,
trusting and relying on each other.

579
00:34:45,641 --> 00:34:48,051
Because of me, you can't
even have a proper wedding.

580
00:34:49,351 --> 00:34:51,681
Ju Ah, I'm sorry.

581
00:34:52,121 --> 00:34:55,821
Not at all. I actually prefer
having a simple ceremony.

582
00:34:56,221 --> 00:34:57,921
Thank you for saying that.

583
00:34:58,291 --> 00:35:00,191
You have to come looking your best
for the wedding.

584
00:35:00,521 --> 00:35:01,761
That will be difficult.

585
00:35:05,901 --> 00:35:07,161
Because I'm already so handsome.

586
00:35:10,031 --> 00:35:11,401
You're quite the joker.

587
00:35:12,271 --> 00:35:14,941
Don't worry about things here.
Just go and enjoy yourselves.

588
00:35:15,741 --> 00:35:16,741
Okay.

589
00:35:17,481 --> 00:35:18,681
Listen...

590
00:35:24,421 --> 00:35:27,251
Thank you so much.

591
00:35:32,621 --> 00:35:34,091
So what should we do for fun today?

592
00:35:34,461 --> 00:35:35,631
Let's play cards today.

593
00:35:36,131 --> 00:35:37,331
They say
it's good for preventing dementia.

594
00:35:38,931 --> 00:35:40,101
You should join us.

595
00:35:40,831 --> 00:35:43,201
I'm very good at it.
You'd better watch out.

596
00:35:48,571 --> 00:35:50,981
Because of my father,

597
00:35:51,441 --> 00:35:54,851
I apologize for having to rush
the wedding like this.

598
00:35:56,151 --> 00:35:59,621
The kids decided it together,
so there's no need to apologize.

599
00:36:00,051 --> 00:36:03,821
By the way, have you two decided
where to go for your honeymoon?

600
00:36:04,291 --> 00:36:07,431
We're planning to go
after Grandfather has recovered.

601
00:36:07,561 --> 00:36:10,731
Oh, you can't do that.
If you postpone your honeymoon,

602
00:36:10,801 --> 00:36:12,201
it'll be hard to go later on.

603
00:36:12,761 --> 00:36:13,761
That's right.

604
00:36:13,831 --> 00:36:16,201
And I hear you're having
a small wedding as it is.

605
00:36:16,731 --> 00:36:19,341
Don't worry about Grandfather.
You should just go.

606
00:36:19,741 --> 00:36:21,541
Okay, then. We'll do that.

607
00:36:22,111 --> 00:36:23,111
Then...

608
00:36:23,911 --> 00:36:25,511
We'll go somewhere domestic.

609
00:36:27,451 --> 00:36:30,581
Do you have a place
in mind for your new home?

610
00:36:32,281 --> 00:36:35,521
Hey, what about Onjeong?

611
00:36:36,191 --> 00:36:40,361
- If you have kids, I could help.
- Well...

612
00:36:40,621 --> 00:36:44,731
- It's too far from their jobs...
- I'd like...

613
00:36:45,461 --> 00:36:47,601
to move in with you.

614
00:36:48,631 --> 00:36:51,841
- What?
- Hey, what are you talking about?

615
00:36:52,171 --> 00:36:53,441
I don't want
to live with our parents.

616
00:36:53,771 --> 00:36:57,311
Well, yes, I mean...

617
00:36:57,441 --> 00:37:01,251
Ju Ah, let's think this
through more carefully.

618
00:37:01,351 --> 00:37:02,351
Since we'll both be working,

619
00:37:02,411 --> 00:37:04,521
I thought it would be hard
to manage the household chores.

620
00:37:04,821 --> 00:37:07,281
So I wanted to ask you
for your help.

621
00:37:07,951 --> 00:37:10,321
Honey, what are you doing?

622
00:37:10,691 --> 00:37:11,691
No, no, it's fine.

623
00:37:12,161 --> 00:37:16,131
- I'm fine with it.
- Well, I'm not. I'll do it. I will.

624
00:37:16,191 --> 00:37:17,561
Let's just do it my way.

625
00:37:19,431 --> 00:37:22,131
Mother, this really wasn't my idea.

626
00:37:24,101 --> 00:37:25,901
Well, my dear...

627
00:37:26,541 --> 00:37:29,241
Our house doesn't really
have a suitable room.

628
00:37:29,841 --> 00:37:31,481
Even Min Seo's room
would be too small.

629
00:37:31,741 --> 00:37:33,981
We can use that room as our bedroom,

630
00:37:34,281 --> 00:37:36,481
and use Ji Hu's room as a study.

631
00:37:37,581 --> 00:37:40,891
I want Ji Hu to spend time
with his aunt and uncle.

632
00:37:42,251 --> 00:37:44,521
Oh my, our daughter-in-law...

633
00:37:45,091 --> 00:37:46,621
You have such a kind heart.

634
00:37:47,191 --> 00:37:50,591
So, what do you think?

635
00:37:50,901 --> 00:37:52,361
Well...

636
00:37:52,901 --> 00:37:55,301
Your sister-in-law
also lives with her in-laws,

637
00:37:55,701 --> 00:37:57,671
and if this is what Ju Ah wants...

638
00:37:58,871 --> 00:38:01,571
I promise
I won't give her a hard time.

639
00:38:02,241 --> 00:38:03,971
Don't you worry.

640
00:38:05,611 --> 00:38:06,881
Right, right.

641
00:38:25,201 --> 00:38:28,301
You won't even need a car here,
right?

642
00:38:28,601 --> 00:38:30,531
You're right,
being right by the subway...

643
00:38:30,531 --> 00:38:32,871
- makes it very accessible.
- It is.

644
00:38:33,241 --> 00:38:35,271
But Mother,
you really did not have to...

645
00:38:35,271 --> 00:38:36,671
renovate the whole interior.

646
00:38:36,741 --> 00:38:39,841
What are you talking about?
It's a newlywed room. Let's redo it.

647
00:38:40,381 --> 00:38:43,751
Take a good look around, my dear.

648
00:38:43,851 --> 00:38:45,451
- Let's go, let's go.
- Okay.

649
00:38:46,351 --> 00:38:47,351
Nice, isn't it?

650
00:38:49,191 --> 00:38:50,221
Ta-da.

651
00:38:50,751 --> 00:38:53,891
Wow, this place is so luxurious.
I love it.

652
00:38:53,961 --> 00:38:58,301
Right? I came here once before,
and I loved that you could see...

653
00:38:58,361 --> 00:39:00,601
and touch all
the interior materials yourself.

654
00:39:02,371 --> 00:39:04,901
While we're redoing your room,

655
00:39:05,271 --> 00:39:06,741
I'd like to redo the kitchen
as well.

656
00:39:07,241 --> 00:39:09,141
Really? Then let's look
at some options together.

657
00:39:09,411 --> 00:39:11,411
Should we? Okay, let's go.

658
00:39:16,981 --> 00:39:18,481
Oh my goodness.

659
00:39:18,821 --> 00:39:22,051
This kitchen furniture
is exactly my style.

660
00:39:22,391 --> 00:39:24,761
But
while this kitchen looks spacious,

661
00:39:24,821 --> 00:39:27,591
shouldn't we see
if it fits our home's layout?

662
00:39:27,631 --> 00:39:30,031
You think so? You're right.

663
00:39:30,091 --> 00:39:32,261
We provide custom designs
for each client,

664
00:39:32,401 --> 00:39:34,701
for a perfect finish
that fits your home's layout.

665
00:39:35,071 --> 00:39:38,271
Excuse me,
I love the color of this kitchen,

666
00:39:38,341 --> 00:39:40,771
can the other rooms
use the same color?

667
00:39:40,871 --> 00:39:43,041
Yes, you can select the same color,

668
00:39:43,141 --> 00:39:44,811
which allows you to create
a cohesive look...

669
00:39:44,881 --> 00:39:45,941
throughout the entire space.

670
00:39:46,481 --> 00:39:49,711
That's great.
We'll look around a bit more then.

671
00:39:50,581 --> 00:39:52,181
- Let's look over here.
- Okay.

672
00:39:59,261 --> 00:40:00,761
They may get along better
than I thought.

673
00:40:01,391 --> 00:40:02,591
That's a relief.

674
00:40:03,431 --> 00:40:05,201
What's with that look?

675
00:40:05,631 --> 00:40:07,801
- Are you jealous?
- No, I'm not.

676
00:40:10,071 --> 00:40:13,071
Hey, what should I do? I have to go.

677
00:40:13,201 --> 00:40:15,541
- What? Why so suddenly?
- Apparently, the restroom...

678
00:40:15,611 --> 00:40:17,271
in the Building A market
is completely clogged.

679
00:40:18,011 --> 00:40:19,581
I'm going to unclog it.

680
00:40:19,681 --> 00:40:23,311
I'll go with you.
You have a weak stomach.

681
00:40:23,381 --> 00:40:24,381
I'll help you.

682
00:40:24,951 --> 00:40:26,421
Seong Mi, can I?

683
00:40:26,681 --> 00:40:30,351
- Go ahead. I'll take care of them.
- Thanks.

684
00:40:30,891 --> 00:40:32,461
Hey, come on, let's go.

685
00:40:32,991 --> 00:40:33,991
Hurry, let's go.

686
00:40:35,131 --> 00:40:36,131
(Younglim Apel Kitchen)

687
00:40:36,231 --> 00:40:37,231
Oh, my.

688
00:40:37,731 --> 00:40:40,031
Oh, my goodness.
Where are they off to?

689
00:40:40,101 --> 00:40:42,801
Oh, it looks like there was
a complaint at the market.

690
00:40:43,101 --> 00:40:44,401
Oh, I see.

691
00:40:46,071 --> 00:40:47,101
Dr. Han.

692
00:40:48,471 --> 00:40:51,511
Are you really okay
with having a small wedding?

693
00:40:51,941 --> 00:40:54,611
- Why?
- You've had a long public career.

694
00:40:55,211 --> 00:40:57,481
I was just worried that
you're rushing because of Father,

695
00:40:57,751 --> 00:40:59,851
and not getting to invite
the guests you want.

696
00:41:00,151 --> 00:41:01,151
Not at all.

697
00:41:01,721 --> 00:41:04,621
After I got sick,
I quit my practice and the show,

698
00:41:04,721 --> 00:41:06,561
so it feels weird to contact people
now.

699
00:41:07,391 --> 00:41:09,261
I'm sure everyone has forgotten me
by now.

700
00:41:16,371 --> 00:41:17,371
My gosh.

701
00:41:19,001 --> 00:41:22,271
It's draining! We unclogged it!

702
00:41:23,241 --> 00:41:27,341
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I've done this before.

703
00:41:27,611 --> 00:41:29,151
This time, it's much easier...

704
00:41:29,481 --> 00:41:31,781
Hey, if you're going to throw up,
do it in there, got it?

705
00:41:31,781 --> 00:41:34,551
- Thanks so much. I'm okay.
- You okay? You okay?

706
00:41:34,621 --> 00:41:36,521
- Yes.
- No, no.

707
00:41:36,851 --> 00:41:38,061
Right, right. Gosh.

708
00:41:38,691 --> 00:41:39,691
Seriously.

709
00:41:40,391 --> 00:41:42,391
This isn't easy. Not easy at all.

710
00:41:42,391 --> 00:41:43,661
(Onjeong Market)

711
00:41:43,661 --> 00:41:46,201
- Man, why does this keep happening?
- I know.

712
00:41:46,261 --> 00:41:47,301
You really had
a rough time yesterday.

713
00:41:47,361 --> 00:41:49,771
- Come on, you had it worse.
- I'll clear it out. I'm sorry.

714
00:41:49,831 --> 00:41:52,371
We already talked about this,
but you're out here again today.

715
00:41:52,441 --> 00:41:53,441
Oh, I'm sorry.

716
00:41:53,501 --> 00:41:55,071
No. Today,
we're confiscating your items...

717
00:41:55,141 --> 00:41:56,141
as per the regulations.

718
00:41:56,211 --> 00:41:58,411
- The inspectors are here again?
- Let go.

719
00:41:58,481 --> 00:42:02,951
- No. Oh, no.
- Oh, my. Hello, everyone.

720
00:42:04,111 --> 00:42:06,281
- Hello there.
- Yes, hello.

721
00:42:06,351 --> 00:42:07,351
Thank you for your hard work.

722
00:42:08,021 --> 00:42:09,551
Well...

723
00:42:09,851 --> 00:42:11,521
Rules are important,

724
00:42:12,021 --> 00:42:15,761
but just kicking out someone
who lives hand-to-mouth like this...

725
00:42:16,061 --> 00:42:18,101
isn't a real solution, is it?

726
00:42:18,601 --> 00:42:21,631
Our instructions are clear.
We can't look the other way anymore.

727
00:42:21,701 --> 00:42:24,841
We're
on the Merchants' Association board.

728
00:42:24,901 --> 00:42:26,941
We'll take responsibility
and make sure...

729
00:42:27,001 --> 00:42:28,511
to find an alternative, okay?

730
00:42:28,841 --> 00:42:29,841
Yes, that's right.

731
00:42:30,441 --> 00:42:33,341
We're going to create a co-op
selling space in the market,

732
00:42:33,481 --> 00:42:35,051
and we're setting it up...

733
00:42:35,111 --> 00:42:37,411
so the street vendors
can operate legally.

734
00:42:38,421 --> 00:42:41,391
We will quickly put
together a proposal...

735
00:42:41,451 --> 00:42:42,891
and bring it to the district office.

736
00:42:42,951 --> 00:42:43,951
Yes, yes.

737
00:42:45,021 --> 00:42:46,061
- Ma'am.
- Yes.

738
00:42:46,161 --> 00:42:49,031
If you're caught again,
we will follow standard procedure.

739
00:42:49,061 --> 00:42:51,531
Yes, okay. Thank you.

740
00:42:51,931 --> 00:42:53,431
- Oh, thank you.
- Thank you.

741
00:42:53,501 --> 00:42:55,731
- Let's go.
- Yes. We will take care of it.

742
00:42:55,801 --> 00:42:56,801
Thank you.

743
00:42:57,201 --> 00:43:01,411
Dr. Gong, thank you.
You used to be the one reporting us.

744
00:43:01,711 --> 00:43:04,041
It seems you've changed.

745
00:43:05,681 --> 00:43:07,211
Did I?

746
00:43:13,121 --> 00:43:15,651
- Hello.
- Oh, Se Ri. What brings you here?

747
00:43:15,721 --> 00:43:17,721
The doctor doesn't have
an appointment today.

748
00:43:17,891 --> 00:43:20,921
I'm holding
a business briefing today.

749
00:43:21,191 --> 00:43:24,761
- You should come with me.
- Why would I go there?

750
00:43:24,901 --> 00:43:27,431
If you're there as Dr. Han Seong Mi,

751
00:43:27,701 --> 00:43:30,831
- it makes me look more impressive.
- Come on.

752
00:43:30,901 --> 00:43:33,401
What? Oh,
please help me out just this once.

753
00:43:33,471 --> 00:43:36,011
I even went with you
to all your hospital appointments.

754
00:43:36,071 --> 00:43:37,411
It's give and take, you know?

755
00:43:38,541 --> 00:43:41,581
- Fine. Let's go.
- Wait...

756
00:43:42,051 --> 00:43:43,751
It's okay.

757
00:43:44,381 --> 00:43:48,291
Then could you please dress up?
And do your prettiest makeup.

758
00:43:48,551 --> 00:43:50,421
The more glamorous, the better.

759
00:43:54,121 --> 00:43:56,661
