970
00:54:49,351 --> 00:54:52,581
Hey, just show me with your fingers.

971
00:54:52,721 --> 00:54:55,691
- I'm scared.
- Okay. I'll look first.

972
00:54:59,821 --> 00:55:01,421
Is it three percent again?

973
00:55:03,961 --> 00:55:05,901
Four percent?

974
00:55:08,101 --> 00:55:09,201
Thirteen percent.

975
00:55:10,071 --> 00:55:12,571
What? Really?

976
00:55:14,441 --> 00:55:16,611
Father, it's 13 percent.

977
00:55:16,871 --> 00:55:17,871
Well done.

978
00:55:18,511 --> 00:55:21,281
See?
I told you sincerity gets through.

979
00:55:21,711 --> 00:55:23,781
I was just imitating Jeong Han.

980
00:55:24,181 --> 00:55:26,981
No. You were a little off at first,

981
00:55:27,281 --> 00:55:29,391
but later you were
completely sincere.

982
00:55:29,451 --> 00:55:31,621
Thanks, man.
Thank you so much, Jeong Han.

983
00:55:32,761 --> 00:55:34,961
- I told you it would work.
- I know.

984
00:55:35,291 --> 00:55:38,191
Sir, you should head inside.
Hey, Dong Ik.

985
00:55:38,261 --> 00:55:39,701
Thirteen percent is
more than good enough.

986
00:55:41,161 --> 00:55:45,841
- What in the world?
- Wow. Ms. Gong.

987
00:55:46,971 --> 00:55:49,011
- You look so pretty.
- It suits you so well.

988
00:55:49,171 --> 00:55:52,111
Thanks. The dress is so beautiful.

989
00:55:53,341 --> 00:55:56,351
- It's exactly what I imagined.
- Thank you.

990
00:55:56,851 --> 00:55:59,381
All right, here comes the groom.

991
00:56:16,801 --> 00:56:20,171
A perfect couple.
A match made in heaven.

992
00:56:24,771 --> 00:56:25,781
Ju Ah.

993
00:56:26,581 --> 00:56:27,711
Mom.

994
00:56:28,441 --> 00:56:30,051
- Mother.
- Oh my.

995
00:56:30,151 --> 00:56:32,281
Oh, you're so pretty, my girl.

996
00:56:33,451 --> 00:56:34,681
You look so handsome, son.

997
00:56:35,291 --> 00:56:36,651
He certainly is. My son.

998
00:56:42,791 --> 00:56:46,261
Now, for our groom, Yang Hyun Bin,
and our bride, Gong Ju Ah,

999
00:56:46,331 --> 00:56:48,461
we're here to bless
their new beginning.

1000
00:56:48,531 --> 00:56:52,041
A warm welcome to all our guests
who have made it here today.

1001
00:56:52,401 --> 00:56:56,071
I am today's MC, a close friend
of the bride and groom,

1002
00:56:56,271 --> 00:56:59,211
and a designer at Taehan Fashion,
Hwangbo Jun Hyeok.

1003
00:56:59,281 --> 00:57:00,311
It's great to see you all.

1004
00:57:00,881 --> 00:57:03,481
- Go, Jun Hyeok!
- Go, Jun Hyeok!

1005
00:57:04,911 --> 00:57:06,121
He's so handsome.

1006
00:57:07,521 --> 00:57:10,821
All right, shall we bring out
today's happy couple?

1007
00:57:11,351 --> 00:57:13,261
The bride and groom will now enter.

1008
00:57:22,531 --> 00:57:24,931
She's so pretty.

1009
00:57:26,601 --> 00:57:29,111
- He's so handsome.
- She's so pretty.

1010
00:57:35,551 --> 00:57:36,911
Yes, as their first love
comes to fruition, the groom's...

1011
00:57:36,981 --> 00:57:39,121
- overwhelming emotions...
- You look great.

1012
00:57:39,581 --> 00:57:41,251
are truly palpable.

1013
00:57:41,781 --> 00:57:44,221
And our bride looks
absolutely overjoyed as well.

1014
00:57:45,621 --> 00:57:46,791
You look great.

1015
00:57:53,331 --> 00:57:54,431
She's so pretty.

1016
00:57:55,631 --> 00:57:56,631
All right, dear guests,

1017
00:57:56,771 --> 00:58:00,441
please give another big round
of applause for our happy couple.

1018
00:58:04,811 --> 00:58:06,041
They look so good together.

1019
00:58:07,011 --> 00:58:09,611
Looking sharp.

1020
00:58:10,051 --> 00:58:11,251
She's so beautiful.

1021
00:58:40,041 --> 00:58:41,141
Look how happy he is.

1022
00:58:42,281 --> 00:58:44,051
Let's go.

1023
00:58:49,491 --> 00:58:51,851
Next,
in place of an officiant's address,

1024
00:58:51,921 --> 00:58:53,291
the bride's grandfather,

1025
00:58:53,361 --> 00:58:55,491
Mr. Gong Gi Cheol,
will give a congratulatory speech.

1026
00:58:55,561 --> 00:58:57,461
Please welcome him
with a big round of applause.

1027
00:59:06,101 --> 00:59:07,671
If I had stayed locked up,

1028
00:59:08,501 --> 00:59:11,141
I would have missed
my granddaughter's wedding.

1029
00:59:16,381 --> 00:59:19,051
It's a joke. You can laugh.

1030
00:59:22,951 --> 00:59:25,121
The years I can never get back...

1031
00:59:25,491 --> 00:59:27,061
What good does it do to regret them?

1032
00:59:28,061 --> 00:59:29,661
Living like this, day by day,

1033
00:59:30,361 --> 00:59:32,531
makes me truly happy.

1034
00:59:33,131 --> 00:59:34,731
After all, what is happiness?

1035
00:59:35,501 --> 00:59:37,801
For me,
when I wake up in the morning...

1036
00:59:38,401 --> 00:59:42,541
and smell soybean paste stew,
I couldn't be happier.

1037
00:59:44,241 --> 00:59:48,741
And having a family that greets me
when I say I am home.

1038
00:59:49,581 --> 00:59:52,551
Having a family to laugh with
while watching TV...

1039
00:59:52,781 --> 00:59:55,121
That's true happiness.

1040
00:59:55,891 --> 00:59:57,051
So, everyone,

1041
00:59:57,621 --> 01:00:00,561
don't just cherish the special days.

1042
01:00:01,121 --> 01:00:05,531
Cherish the ordinary days,
each and every one.

1043
01:00:06,301 --> 01:00:10,101
Because on any given day
in our lives,

1044
01:00:10,171 --> 01:00:13,571
no one knows what might happen.

1045
01:00:14,741 --> 01:00:17,611
To the bride and groom,
and to everyone here,

1046
01:00:18,541 --> 01:00:21,911
I hope you laugh a lot today
and laugh a lot tomorrow.

1047
01:00:22,281 --> 01:00:25,581
Let's all be as happy
as we can be for as long as we live.

1048
01:00:26,751 --> 01:00:28,051
I wish you both happiness.

1049
01:00:37,291 --> 01:00:38,291
Father.

1050
01:00:44,571 --> 01:00:45,641
(Yang Hyun Bin, Gong Ju Ah)

1051
01:01:06,921 --> 01:01:08,791
Let's have everyone gather
in a little closer.

1052
01:01:09,261 --> 01:01:10,291
And the person in the middle,

1053
01:01:10,291 --> 01:01:11,391
move a bit more to the center,
please?

1054
01:01:11,391 --> 01:01:12,901
- Yes.
- Yes.

1055
01:01:13,031 --> 01:01:16,031
By the way,
who's catching the bouquet today?

1056
01:01:17,531 --> 01:01:20,801
- We haven't decided.
- I will.

1057
01:01:22,041 --> 01:01:23,141
I'll catch it.

1058
01:01:24,971 --> 01:01:26,041
Wait a minute.

1059
01:01:34,881 --> 01:01:38,691
- Oh Jin Ah.
- Oh Jin Ah.

1060
01:01:38,691 --> 01:01:40,191
- Shin Bo Mi.
- Shin Bo Mi.

1061
01:01:40,521 --> 01:01:41,761
- Shin Bo Mi.
- Shin Bo Mi.

1062
01:01:42,161 --> 01:01:43,731
- Shin Bo Mi.
- Bo Mi. You have to get married.

1063
01:01:43,791 --> 01:01:44,791
- Shin Bo Mi.
- Shin Bo Mi.

1064
01:01:46,031 --> 01:01:47,031
Ready.

1065
01:01:47,731 --> 01:01:48,731
There it goes.

1066
01:01:52,601 --> 01:01:53,601
I'll get it.

1067
01:01:55,941 --> 01:01:57,971
- Oh my.
- Oh dear.

1068
01:02:00,581 --> 01:02:01,711
Looks like she's getting married.

1069
01:02:02,281 --> 01:02:03,581
- CEO.
- CEO.

1070
01:02:03,851 --> 01:02:06,381
- CEO.
- CEO.

1071
01:02:15,761 --> 01:02:16,761
Seon Chul.

1072
01:02:17,531 --> 01:02:18,561
Are you okay?

1073
01:02:19,631 --> 01:02:21,131
I'm okay.

1074
01:02:29,141 --> 01:02:31,341
(Yang Hyun Bin, Gong Ju Ah)

1075
01:02:31,341 --> 01:02:34,311
(Thank You
For Celebrating Our Wedding)

1076
01:02:37,611 --> 01:02:38,611
Drink this.

1077
01:02:46,491 --> 01:02:47,761
Thanks.

1078
01:02:51,131 --> 01:02:52,131
What are you smiling about?

1079
01:02:53,561 --> 01:02:55,671
Are you thinking that
you can die happy now?

1080
01:02:56,471 --> 01:02:57,471
No.

1081
01:02:59,701 --> 01:03:01,501
It's just so nice.

1082
01:03:03,941 --> 01:03:06,241
It feels good to be alive.

1083
01:03:07,381 --> 01:03:08,481
I'm glad.

1084
01:03:09,381 --> 01:03:10,551
Gi Cheol.

1085
01:03:11,751 --> 01:03:12,881
I...

1086
01:03:14,821 --> 01:03:16,651
want to see
Dong Ik win the election,

1087
01:03:17,121 --> 01:03:18,291
and see Dong Suk...

1088
01:03:19,161 --> 01:03:21,621
have her baby.

1089
01:03:22,261 --> 01:03:25,801
Of course you will.
That goes without saying.

1090
01:03:27,561 --> 01:03:28,561
Yes.

1091
01:03:29,331 --> 01:03:30,431
I...

1092
01:03:31,731 --> 01:03:33,141
want to live.

1093
01:03:37,971 --> 01:03:39,541
I really want to live.

1094
01:03:48,221 --> 01:03:52,791
Newlyweds, I'll drive you
safely to the airport.

1095
01:03:53,061 --> 01:03:54,061
All right.

1096
01:03:55,161 --> 01:03:59,501
- This is exhausting. Never again.
- What?

1097
01:04:00,631 --> 01:04:02,231
Hey, watch how you talk...

1098
01:04:03,501 --> 01:04:05,301
So you'd better be good to me.
Got it?

1099
01:04:07,271 --> 01:04:10,471
What will you do,
being so henpecked already?

1100
01:04:10,541 --> 01:04:14,481
- I'm just pretending to be. See?
- Oh, really?

1101
01:04:18,911 --> 01:04:19,921
Yes, Father.

1102
01:04:22,791 --> 01:04:23,791
What?

1103
01:04:26,791 --> 01:04:28,191
What's wrong with Father?

1104
01:04:29,391 --> 01:04:31,531
Jun Hyeok,
can you bring the car around?

1105
01:04:31,831 --> 01:04:33,131
Okay.

1106
01:04:33,531 --> 01:04:36,401
Grandfather collapsed.

1107
01:04:37,601 --> 01:04:38,601
What?

1108
01:04:48,081 --> 01:04:50,681
(Recipe For Love)

1109
01:04:50,781 --> 01:04:53,821
Seon Chul's breathing
was getting more and more ragged.

1110
01:04:53,881 --> 01:04:56,221
What if the transplant goes wrong?

1111
01:04:56,321 --> 01:04:59,421
If he's going to die anyway,
we must try.

1112
01:04:59,421 --> 01:05:00,491
- Yang Dong Ik.
- Yang Dong Ik.

1113
01:05:00,491 --> 01:05:02,991
Father would've loved to see this.

1114
01:05:03,191 --> 01:05:06,201
As of today, I've been transferred
to the Food Business Division.

1115
01:05:06,261 --> 01:05:08,831
One of you will be appointed
as the new managing director.

1116
01:05:09,401 --> 01:05:13,401
Seong Mi must be nervous.
It's been ages since her live show.

1117
01:05:13,471 --> 01:05:15,471
I prescribe a recipe for love.

1118
01:05:16,206 --> 01:05:17,906
Dramaday.me
